<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2847&amp;p=20861#p20861"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[TV 600x475 ?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2847&amp;p=20861#p20861"><![CDATA[
When I video capture the Super Mario Bros. title screen, the minimum rectangle containing everything on screen except the blue border is 589x448. The source NES image in this case is 256x224 pixels. So for my capture, the horizontal is being scaled by 2.3 and the vertical by 2.0, for an H/V ratio of 1.15.<br /><br />A video capture might get slightly different widths, the same way the image on a TV will vary from one set to another.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Tue Jan 02, 2007 8:52 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
